<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In June 2022, as crypto prices spi=
raled and Alameda=E2=80=99s lenders were calling in their loans, [Caroline]=
 Ellison said she prepared seven =E2=80=9Calternative balance sheets=E2=80=
=9D that would conceal Alameda=E2=80=99s large borrowing from FTX customers=
, in response to a request for financial information from one of its lender=
s, Genesis. Alameda had borrowed around $10 billion from FTX customers and =
had loaned around $5 billion to FTX executives and affiliated entities. =E2=
=80=9CHe suggested I should prepare some alternative ways of presenting the=
 information and send it to him,=E2=80=9D she said. =E2=80=9CI understood h=
im to be directing me to come up with ways to conceal things in our balance=
 sheet we both agreed would look bad.=E2=80=9D Bankman-Fried told her to se=
nd Genesis her Alternative 7 =E2=80=94 which didn=E2=80=99t disclose money =
taken from FTX customers. It cut Alameda=E2=80=99s liabilities from $15 bil=
lion to around $10 billion. She testified that the document was =E2=80=9Cdi=
shonest.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you prepare a balance sheet for a lender an=
d your boss says =E2=80=9Cwhy don=E2=80=99t we present this information in =
a different way,=E2=80=9D you probably need a lawyer. If you prepare SEVEN =
BALANCE SHEETS and your boss is like =E2=80=9Clet=E2=80=99s go with Alterna=
tive 7=E2=80=9D then one of you is going to prison absolutely forever. Caro=
line Ellison smartly decided it wasn=E2=80=99t going to be her.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ellison, the chief executive officer of Sam Ba=
nkman-Fried=E2=80=99s crypto trading firm Alameda Research,=C2=A0has been <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33007895.258422/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMTEvY2Fyb2xpbm=
