 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">this week</a>. Bankman-Fried=
=E2=80=99s defense, in the press and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/33007895.258422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNv=
bS9zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1wbGFubmVkLXRlc3RpbW9ueS1mdWxsLXRleHQtZnR4LTIwMjI=
tMTI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb5a716ca" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">to Congress</a> and in his =
lawyer=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
3007895.258422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tLzIwMjMvMTAvNC8yMzkwMzk4Ni9z=
YW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1vcGVuaW5nLXN0YXRlbWVudHMtdHJpYWwtZnJhdWQ/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cBb24f7791" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">opening statement</a>, has been something t=
o the effect of, sure, FTX made some mistakes and lost some customer money,=
 but it was all a series of good-faith accidents; we were just kids who did=
n=E2=80=99t know what we were doing. We innocently lost track of the money.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And in fact it=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>seem li=
ke FTX couldn=E2=80=99t keep track of its money. When it filed for bankrupt=
cy, John Ray (who ran Enron=E2=80=99s bankruptcy) came in as CEO and <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33007895.258422/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTcvbWF0dC1sZXZ=
pbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1mdHgtd2FzLW5vdC12ZXJ5LWNhcmVmdWw_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxMj=
IzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX=
3Rlcm09MjMxMDEyJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7c=
e2e3ea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> filed a very grumpy report</a> saying =E2=80=9CNever in my=
 career have I seen such a complete failure of corporate controls and such =
a complete absence of trustworthy financial information as occurred here=E2=
=80=9D and complaining that FTX executives =E2=80=9Capproved disbursements =
by responding with personalized emojis=E2=80=9D on Slack. And when Bankman-=
Fried was trying to stave off bankruptcy last November, he <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33007895.258422/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1za=
GVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTIyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwm=
dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTAxMiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXl=
zdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4dabb4ea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> circulated a spreadshee=
t</a>=C2=A0listing FTX=E2=80=99s assets and liabilities =E2=80=94=C2=A0a =
=E2=80=9Cbalance sheet,=E2=80=9D I and others called it, though it was not =
laid out anything like a traditional balance sheet =E2=80=94=C2=A0with an $=
8 billion entry for =E2=80=9CHidden, poorly internally labeled =E2=80=98fia=
t@=E2=80=99 account.=E2=80=9D The defense is that they forgot that $8 billi=
on was missing, because they were bad at spreadsheets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look: The proper number of balance sheets is o=
ne.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Zero is very bad! At some level I can see =E2=80=9Cwe were carele=
ss kids and we never could keep track of how much money we had=E2=80=9D as =
a partial defense to fraud charges. I don=E2=80=99t think it works =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0I think FTX=C2=A0<em>represented=C2=A0</em>that it was being caref=
ul with money, and if it wasn=E2=80=99t that=E2=80=99s fraud =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0but it has an intuitive appeal.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seven is much worse! That=E2=80=99s not =E2=80=
=9Cwe couldn=E2=80=99t keep track of our money, oops.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=
=99s =E2=80=9Cwe had lots of different ways to keep track of our money, dep=
ending on the audience, and=C2=A0we kept coming up with new ways until we g=
ot one that looked good.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s not =E2=80=9Cwe misplaced =
our money carelessly=E2=80=9D; that=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cwe misplaced our mon=
ey and then very carefully covered it up.=E2=80=9D Zero balance sheets is h=
apless fraud; seven balance sheets is calculating fraud.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Somehow the story gets worse. For one thing: I=
t=E2=80=99s eight? =E2=80=9CSeven alternative balance sheets,=E2=80=9D plus=
 the main one.=C2=A0Molly White <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/33007895.258422/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzbGV0dGVyLm1vbGx5d2hpdGUubmV0L=
3AvdGhlLWZ0eC10cmlhbC1kYXktc2l4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB357d6222" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
has the spreadsheets</a>; the alts are different tabs in the Google Sheet.=
=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe =E2=80=98main=E2=80=99=C2=A0spreadsheet was only used in=
ternally, as it accurately reflected Alameda=E2=80=99s terrible financial p=
osition,=E2=80=9D White writes. I mean, not <em>that=C2=A0</em>terrible, in=
 June 2022: It shows $21.1 billion of assets, $14.9 billion of liabilities =
and a net asset value of $6.2 billion. The spreadsheets have quadrants for =
liquid assets, liquid (i.e. short-term) liabilities, long-term assets and l=
ong-term liabilities.=C2=A0The liquid=C2=A0liabilities here include=C2=A0$9=
.9 billion of =E2=80=9Cexchange borrows=E2=80=9D;=C2=A0the long-term assets=
 include $4.6 billion of =E2=80=9Crelated party loans.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Alternative 7, the one they sent to Genesis, d=
eletes the related party loans entirely, because they look bad, reducing Al=
ameda=E2=80=99s assets from $21.1 billion to $16.5 billion. It keeps the ne=
t asset value the same, at $6.2 billion, and solves for this by reducing th=
e liabilities to $10.3 billion. It deletes the entry for =E2=80=9Cexchange =
borrows,=E2=80=9D reducing Alameda=E2=80=99s displayed short-term borrowing=
 from $10.7 billion (=E2=80=9Cexchange borrows=E2=80=9D plus =E2=80=9COT lo=
ans,=E2=80=9D i.e. open term loans) to $1.8 billion (just the OT loans). It=
 combines the $9.9 billion of exchange borrowing with $2.9 billion of longe=
r-term loans to get, uh, well, my math would say that=E2=80=99s $12.8 billi=
on of loans, but Alternative 7 reports $8.2 billion of loans. The differenc=
e is $4.6 billion, which is exactly what they lopped off the assets by dele=
ting the related party loans.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The result is a balance sheet that is less lev=
ered (liabilities of 63% of assets instead of 71%) and more liquid (liquid =
assets of 395% of =E2=80=9Cliquid liabilities,=E2=80=9D instead of just 61%=
).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Which seems like fraud. Possibly more offensiv=
e is the fact that they seem to have=C2=A0started with a net asset value of=
 $6.2 billion and USED THE ENTRY FOR =E2=80=9CLOANS=E2=80=9D AS A PLUG.=C2=
=A0I am not an accountant or anything but I will say that the=C2=A0<em>good=
=C2=A0</em>way to do a balance sheet is:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Add up your assets.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Add up your liabilities.</li>=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">Subtract the liabilities from the assets to get your net as=
set value.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And a bad way would be:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Start with the net asset value you wan=
t.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Add up your assets.</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Delete the=C2=A0embarrassing ones.</li>=09<li=
 style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Subtract the assets you have left=C2=A0from =
your net asset value to get your liabilities.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">Just make up some numbers for individual liabilities to get the=
 right total.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My conclusion from this is that FTX was in fac=
t extremely bad at accounting, but not in a charming innocent way.</p>
